...
User enters prompt
...
1. Count all closing-parentheses in the prompt and save their indexes in the array
2. Create and initialize the object s_engine_data structure and some auxiliary variables
3. Call parser_engine()

parser_engine()

1. Traverse the prompt string character by character

2. IF we encounter a letter-operand (excluding spaces)
    2.1. Add this letter to the `ops` array (array of operands)
    2.2. Check what symbol follows the letter (excluding spaces)

        2.2.1. IF the symbol following the letter is a pipe '|'
            2.2.2. Create a pipe
            2.2.3. Add this pipe to the array of all pipes
            2.2.4. IF the operand before this pipe is the first operand found
                2.2.4.1. Set the read-end (stdin) of this operand to -1 (no-pipe value)
            2.2.5. ELSE (this is not the first operand)
                2.2.5.1 Set the read-end (stdin) of this operand to the index of the previous pipe
            2.2.6. Set the write-end (stdout) of this operand the index of the newly created pipe
            2.2.7. IF an opening-parenthesis '(' appears after the pipe

                2.2.7.1. Add the prompt index of this parenthesis to the array of all opening-parentheses
                2.2.7.2. Increment the opening-parentheses counter
                2.2.7.3. Move the prompt index `pi` to the first symbol after '('
                2.2.7.4. Call parser_engine()
                2.2.7.5. IF the array of closing-parentheses is empty
                    2.2.7.5.1. Parsing error
                2.2.7.6. ELSE (the array is not empty)
                    2.2.7.6.1. Find in the closing-parentheses array the nearest unmarked ')' corresponding to the last opening-parenthesis '('
                    2.2.7.6.2. Move the prompt index `pi` to the index of this ')' plus 1
                    2.2.7.6.3. Mark this ')' as closed
                    2.2.7.6.4. Decrement the opening-parentheses counter (remove the last element from the opening-parentheses array)
                    2.2.7.6.5. Retrieve the exit code of the last executed letter-operand
                    2.2.7.6.6. JUMP to step 1 (continue traversing the prompt)

        2.2.2. IF the symbol following the letter is a closing-parenthesis ')'
            2.2.2.1. IF the opening-parentheses array is empty
                2.2.2.1.1. Parsing error
            2.2.2.2. ELSE
                2.2.2.2.1. JUMP to step 1
                
3. IF we encounter a non-letter symbol (excluding spaces)

    3.1. IF this symbol is an opening-parenthesis '('

		3.1.1 Add the prompt index of this parenthesis to the opening-parentheses array
		3.1.2. Increment the opening-parentheses counter
		3.1.3. Move the prompt index `pi` to the first symbol after '('
		3.1.4. Call parser_engine()
		3.1.5. IF the closing-parentheses array is empty
			3.1.5.1. Parsing error
		3.1.6. ELSE
			3.1.6.1. Find the nearest unmarked closing-parenthesis ')' corresponding to the last opening-parenthesis 
			3.1.6.2. Move the prompt index `pi` on the index of this ')' + plus one
			3.1.6.3. Mark this ')' as closed
			3.1.6.4. Decrement the opening-parentheses counter (remove the last element from the opening-parentheses array)
			3.1.6.5. Retrieve the exit code of the last executed letter-operand
			3.1.6.6. JUMP to step 1 (continue traversing the prompt)

    3.2. IF this symbol we encountered is closing-parenthesis ')'

		3.2.1. IF the opening-parentheses array is empty
			3.2.1.1. Parsing error
		3.2.2. ELSE
			3.2.2.1. JUMP to step 1

	3.3. IF the symbol is a pipe '|'
		
		3.3.1. IF the operands array is empty
			3.3.1.1. Parsing error
		3.3.2. ELSE
			3.3.2.1. Create a pipe
			3.3.2.2. Add this pipe to pipes array
			3.3.2.3. Assign the read-end (stdin) of the last operand to the index of the previous pipe
			3.3.2.4. Assign the write-end (stdout) of the last operand the index of the current pipe
			3.3.2.5. Increment the pipe index
			3.3.2.6. Increment the operand index
			3.3.2.7. JUMP to step 1 (continue traversal)

	3.4. ELSE (any other symbol)
		3.4.1. Parsing error

end of parser_engine()
